                android:layout_centerHorizontal="true"
                android:layout_gravity="center_horizontal" />

            <ImageView
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:id="@+id/parippuvada2"
                android:layout_below="@+id/parippuvada11"
                android:src="@drawable/parippuvada"


                />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:text="INGREDIENTS:\n\n
•	Toor Daal (Tuvara parippu) or Chena Daal-1 cup\n
•	Ginger-1 small piece(finely chopped)\n
•	Green Chilly-2 (finely chopped)\n
•	Curry leaves -1 spring\n
•	Small onion -15 finely chopped\n
•	Crushed red chilly-2tsp\n
•	Salt- to taste\n
•	Coconut Oil-for frying\n\n
METHOD:\n
1.	Wash the daal and soak for 1 hour.Drain and keep aside for 1  more hour.\n
2.	Here I used toor daal..I don’t have grinder so took small jar of the blender.\n
3.	Grind the daal into coarse paste\n
4.	No need to add water..b4 grinding take 2 tbsp of daal and keep aside.\n
5.	To the ground daal add 2 tbsp of daal, salt,onion,ginger,green chilly,curry leaves and dry red chilly.\n
6.	Mix finely and keep aside for 10 minutes.\n
7.	Heat oil in a pan..\n
8.	Then make dough in to small balls .wet ur palm and flatten it by pressing with other plam just like making cutlets.\n
9.	Shape the vada as u want (i mean thick or thin)\n
10.	Drop each vada to the hot oil and deep fry them by flipping each sides.
Cook until vada is cooked both inside and outside .Transfer into kitchen tissue and serve with hot tea or coffee..\n


"
                android:id="@+id/parippuvada3"
